          "_key": "e23db8a92066",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "Now, youâ€™ve got to understand that I was born in the â€™50s, grew up in the â€™60s, and played in a rock band five nights a week throughout the â€™70s. Guys like Rick Wakeman (Yes) and Keith Emerson (ELP) were my influences, as were bands like Gentle Giant and Genesis. Iâ€™ve been searching for VST instruments that emulate keyboards like the Mellotron, Rhodes, B3, Clav, Minimoog, etc., that I used to own and play (I still have my B3 and Minimoog)."
