        {
          "_key": "80cab0e2df85",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "For a while, I got into Virtual Instruments (VSTi) to record with, and it was nice to have all the keyboards I once owned or could never have owned available at my fingertips to compose with. I still have vintage keys, like my Hammond B3, Minimoog, Polymoog, EMU Proteus/1, ESQ-1, Yamaha TX7s, and Roland MKB-300 MIDI Controller. Thereâ€™s something about having the hardware that virtual instruments canâ€™t replace."
