      "children": [
        {
          "_key": "26ea63f6b7c1",
          "_type": "span",
          "marks": [],
          "text": "I like to write in sections and then arrange those sections into a song. ACID makes this easy because its loop-based approach allows me to record a verse or chorus once and reuse it as many times as I want. You can quickly throw a song together and hear how it will sound. Since I write alone, itâ€™s great to have Mick Fleetwood lay down a drum track and Rudy Sarzo a bass track to inspire me. ðŸ˜‰ Of course, Iâ€™m referring to the ability to purchase loops from other musicians and use them in your compositions royalty-free. Usually, when working in a band, someone plays a riff that inspires a jam, which eventually turns into a song. ACID Loops provide that same kind of interactive inspiration."
        }
